<item>
            <title>[FLINK-2519] BarrierBuffers get stuck infinitely when some inputs end early</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2519</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When some sources exit early, the barrier buffer may start an alignment, but will never complete it, because some inputs never deliver a checkpoint barrier.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2515&quot; title=&quot;CheckpointCoordinator triggers checkpoints even if not all sources are running any more&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-2515&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-2515&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; mitigates most of the problem, by not starting checkpoints any more when some sources already finished. When a checkpoint is started while a source is finishing, the barrier buffer may still align infinitely.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
